name: Patti Thompson
tweet: @ReneeAlida My Stenosis and DDD caused permanent nerve damage in left extremities. Prescribed Neurontin for neuropathy and nerve pain and that was even worse.

name: Brad
tweet: @ReneeAlida I was on a high dose of neurontin, I got so confused I would get off the bus in front of my apartment building and not know where I was. tweet: @DrLanthois @ravensspirit68 Could you show me the randomized controlled trials on the long term effectiveness of cymbalta use in chronic non-cancer pain? How about lyrica or neurontin? Celebrex?

name: ⚖️ Renee...I am not a cat (or am I?)
tweet: @Lupus_Chat When I was 1st diagnosed yrs ago, the combo of meds I was on: prednisone, neurontin, lyrica etc - I rapidly gained 80 lbs. I was always SO hungry! I've switched docs and changed up meds as much as poss. My app is usually normal but still hard to lose. Pain makes exercise hard.

name: Linda Giles
tweet: That is so true. For me, these have the least side effects. Neurontin and Lyrica were intolerable to me. If they'd had an effect on the pain I might have been able to put up with it. But these were bad all the way around. There is no high associated with my pain meds.

name: Bryan Minarsky
tweet: @sleepybostonian While I admire your attention to dangers in OTC drugs, Ibuprofen doesn't cause thinner blood or a delay in clotting.  Ibuprofen, Naproxen and in some lucky people, nerve pain drugs (Neurontin, Gabapentin, Pregabalin) are great for your needs.  Acetaminophen is the real danger!

name: Carroll S. Jones

tweet: @DebraWinterroth @HilaryKimMorden @painadvocateAR Lyrica & Neurontin (gabapentin) both make me jittery as hell & sick to my stomach. Think I WANTED to be physically dependent on morphine? name: ♡ Amanda ♡
tweet: First dose of Neurontin did nothing, far from even touching my pain or feeling it at all. I took the second dose a bit early. Eh, I don't know what I'm feeling but it's immensely little. Very slight. More so, sleepy. At least I don't feel the pain when I sleep.

name: ♡ Amanda ♡
tweet: Neurontin, always knew it was fickle but never thought it would just abruptly stop. Over the weekend I only took 1/3 of the dosage to break tolerance, couldn't quit fully due to pain hoping I'd feel it still. Nothing. So far nothing, took it 2 hours ago.

name: ♡ Amanda ♡
tweet: The dreaded tale of Monday blues strikes once again.   Only this time it manifests physically in #pain, maximum on the scale, I'm sick it feels like I'm going to vomit. Arthritis started acting up.   If my Neurontin doesn't work today than I dunno what I'm going to do.

tweet: @EmmaSkywalkerO @Corky73851098 Did the vet think it might be Syringiomyelia? They do treat it with neurontin, also Omeprazole, and sometimes prednisolone. We gave our Cadie tramadol when she had extra pain too.

name: Emma M&M Luke Skywalker
tweet: @Corky73851098 Yes, my vet is a sweet lady and she did some imaging and other tests. I have some narrowing in the L4/L5 disc area, so she gave neurontin for nerve pain and rimadyl for musculoskeletal pain. It helps, but I might have overdone it on my walk and by jumping around the house.🤸🏻‍♂️🤾‍♀️🛋

name: Gracey
tweet: If a medical professional ever suggests putting you on gabapentin / Neurontin please run for the hills. I’m weening myself off them and honestly, I feel like I’m dying. My brain actually feels as though it’s buzzing 😭

name: Néstor Carrasquero
tweet: A ese, a ese no se lo gana nadie, jajajaja. El propio Neurontín

name: Boone
tweet: @TerriMe3 @Elianok10 For anyone wondering what the #FDA indications & side effects are for Gabapentin/Neurontin:   https://t.co/nuCDWUn3BZ

name: ♡ Amanda ♡
tweet: Today has certainly taken it's toll physically and currently mentally. Neurontin, first dose yielded no results. Didn't even barely feel it, nothing. On my second dose. Joints and feet are hurting so bad. Uncomfortable to even set with my right leg bent. No resolve for feet.

name: ♡ Amanda ♡
tweet: Sometimes you just have to walk off and let the subject that you're heart has hardened about physically & mentally let go of the comments that were made regarding it. Which I'm trying so hard to do, the mental part. Neurontin would help but it's not working for me today.

name: Marissa Y
tweet: https://t.co/IJttmarC1E Prescribed by doctors & neurologists very frequently but in a nutshell, there’s limited evidence to support they work for many conditions, and there can be some harmful side effects, like somnolence, dizziness and difficulty walking #gabapentin #neurontin

name: Doesnt Sleep
tweet: @johncardillo Looks like Neurontin side effects for some people, to me. And if she drinks wine with that, it's worse. I have to wonder if she is drinking her wine to help with Neurontin side effects. JMO

name: Doesnt Sleep
tweet: @DeeEscalante @DawsonInga She looks and acts like I did on Neurontin but I had weird arm movements and was dancing up and down when I walked too. It was exhausting, and so embarrassing I stopped going anywhere.

name: Tara Montgomery
tweet: This is a timely reminder about the off-label use issues that my team at CR Best Buy Drugs reported on with an AG consumer education grant from the Neurontin settlement over 10 years ago. The irony is not lost on me that today our vet prescribed Gabapentin off-label for my cat.

name: Doesnt Sleep
tweet: @JoeAllenNewman Tired of treated like criminals, folks like me on Medicare & Medicaid that have done all the procedures & have only opioids left that work, give up go home to bed & stay there rather than be forced to take other meds like Neurontin that affect us badly. We aren't their $ Pt's.

name: Doesnt Sleep
tweet: @marygerdt @SpeakerPelosi Could be. Neurontin had me stuttering, searching for common words, unable to carry a thought to completion Sounded drunk and walked like a meth head. I stopped going anywhere it was so embarrassing. AntiD's just turn me into a zombie. None of which fits my type A personality, LOL

name: LostAddicted
tweet: @CrashJes I take Norco along with Neurontin for MS pain. I've never heard of this medication. I'll look it up but I agree with you on being leery about it.

name: Doesnt Sleep
tweet: @marygerdt @SpeakerPelosi Tellin ya', I don't think it is just her dentures slipping. She acts and talks like I did at the beginning of Neurontin. The  more they upped it the worse I got. Beto and his mealy mouth remind of the same too.

name: Ajaya Lloyd
tweet: @Tha_Mist My doctor suggested I be tested. I don't have the HLA-B27 gene but I do have Ankylosing Spondylitis. I was diagnosed 2 years ago. I am not on any injections. But I do take Neurontin for the nerve pain Along with  Anti inflammatory medications as well.

tweet: Okay, post day exhaustion almost feels okay for the first time in... Years? To be fair, I am on a truck of neurontin and a pint of beer.

name: Cathie Braun
tweet: @JoshBloomACSH @HilaryKimMorden Neurontin is useless! Tried it, dumped it! I'm on a med. that works for me. I've never felt the  need to take more and more. I've lowered my dose as needed, by me! Not tapered. And yes, it's an opiate  the world hates, so Please make a new non addicting one.

name: SJ Gold
tweet: it works REALLY well on my #crps flares. after each surgery the limbs blow up and feel like they will explode w/o gabapentin; saved my behind w/the #rsd attacks. But you are right, neurontin is not any better as a general  #painkiller than opioids are for #neuralgia #crpssucks

name: Lyme disease does NOT exist!
tweet: @JoshBloomACSH @downtowin Everyone I know takes neurontin + opiates. Neurontin isn’t a substitute but a drug to be used in tandem. Imo. It’s a glorified double dose of Benadryl. If Benny’s won’t cut it...chances are Gabapentin won’t either. ♿️ #PainPainPain

tweet: Neurontin - The Darling of The Anti-Opioid Crowd. But Does It Work? -  https://t.co/pQyDBzWTJL #GoogleAlerts

name: Shelley
tweet: @tal7291 @LelenaPeacock Gabapentin is neurontin made for seizures. I was told years ago that it could help my nerve pain from an injury. That stuff is awful. name: NAPLEX Study Guide
tweet: Mechanism of Pregabalin / Gabapentin  Pregabalin (Lyrica) and gabapentin (Neurontin) are structural analogs of GABA, but they do not work by interacting with GABA.  Instead, both drugs act as inhibitors of α2δ subunit-containing voltage-dependent calcium channels (VDCCs).

tweet: Sorry. I don't WANT to ignoring the things and the people. I HAVE to. Again. While watching a movie with the Hubs Tuesday night I had a particularly bad seizure. I slept for 7 solid hours afterwards. I had missed 2 doses of Neurontin. A break from everything is necessary. Peace
